---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About CSVBox Blog" description="Learn about the CSVBox Blog and how we help developers build better data onboarding experiences.">

<section>
  <div class="py-9">
    <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900">About CSVBox Blog</h1>
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-normal text-gray-700">
          The CSVBox Blog is where developers, product teams, and SaaS founders learn how to build better data onboarding experiences.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-normal text-gray-700">
          We share practical insights on spreadsheet imports, validation workflows, product-led growth, and everything that helps your app say <em class="text-primary-500">yes</em> to user data — without writing a backend.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-normal text-gray-700">
          Whether you're scaling a SaaS product or hacking together your first MVP, you'll find technical deep dives, integration guides, and real-world lessons to ship faster and onboard smarter.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-6 bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Our Mission</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">
          We believe data import shouldn't be a barrier to user adoption. Every CSV upload, every spreadsheet transformation, every validation error is an opportunity to either delight your users or frustrate them. Our mission is to help you choose delight.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">What You'll Find Here</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary-500 mr-2">•</span>
              <span><strong>Technical Tutorials:</strong> Step-by-step guides for implementing CSV imports, data validation, and transformation workflows</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary-500 mr-2">•</span>
              <span><strong>Integration Guides:</strong> How to connect CSV imports with popular tools like Zapier, webhooks, and databases</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary-500 mr-2">•</span>
              <span><strong>Best Practices:</strong> Industry insights on user experience, error handling, and data quality</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary-500 mr-2">•</span>
              <span><strong>Case Studies:</strong> Real-world examples of successful data onboarding implementations</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-primary-500 mr-2">•</span>
              <span><strong>Product Updates:</strong> Latest features and improvements to the CSVBox platform</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Who We Write For</h2>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <div class="p-4 bg-primary-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-sm">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Frontend Developers</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Building user-friendly import interfaces without backend complexity</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-4 bg-primary-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-sm">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Product Managers</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Improving user onboarding and reducing support tickets</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-4 bg-primary-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-sm">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">SaaS Founders</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Scaling data imports without hiring a dedicated backend team</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-4 bg-primary-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-sm">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Operations Teams</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Streamlining data workflows and reducing manual processing</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-50 to-blue-50 p-8 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-sm">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Behind the Blog</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-4">
          CSVBox Blog is maintained by the team behind <a href="https://csvbox.io" class="text-primary-500 hover:text-primary-600 underline">CSVBox</a>, 
          the developer-first CSV import tool that helps thousands of applications handle user data imports seamlessly.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          Our insights come from years of solving real-world data import challenges, working with teams from startups to enterprise companies, 
          and constantly iterating on what makes data onboarding truly effortless.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="https://csvbox.io" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-primary-100 text-white rounded-lg border border-primary-500 transition-colors">
            Try CSVBox
          </a>
          <a href="https://help.csvbox.io" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 border border-primary-500 text-primary-500 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-50 transition-colors">
            Read the Docs
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
    